Turkey Plans to Develop 300-Megawatt Hydroelectric Project in Madagascar

-- B y   H a n n a h   M c N e i s h
-- 
2011-05-11T05:05:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/turkey-plans-to-develop-300-megawatt-hydro-electricity-plant-in-madagascar.html
Turkey  plans to develop a 300-
megawatt hydropower plant in  Madagascar , Turkish President
 Abdullah Gul  said.  The facility will be built at Mahavola, 150 kilometers (93
miles) west of the capital, Antananarivo, Gul said in a
statement e-mailed by Madagascar’s presidency yesterday. Gul met
Madagascar’s president,  Andry Rajoelina , at a conference in
Istanbul yesterday, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah McNeish in Antananarivo at 
 hmcneish@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  